               <head>Miscellaneous works on geometry, 8 items (a-h)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85054134 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068424">
                  <summary>Composite volume comprising miscellaneous works on geometry. Volume not dated; item a dated (28 Ramaz̤ān 1143/6 April 1731). Scribal nastaʿlīq and naskh, by multiple hands. Annotations. Partial foliation in pencil alongside earlier intermittent Persian foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (pasteboards edged with brown leather, covered with a burnt umber-coloured coarse cotton textile); labels. Folios mostly bound; cropped, stained, wormholes, later repairs. Condition poor.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="14r">ff. 1v-14r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(a), ff. 1v-14r.</p>
                        <p>Persian translation by 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100043782133.0x000001 viaf_51546611" role="aut">Imām al-Dīn [Riyāz̤ī] ibn Luṭf Allāh [Muhandis Dihlavī Darbī]</persName>of an earlier Arabic compendium on Euclid, the 
                <title key="work_23021">Ashkāl al-taʾsīs</title>by 
                <persName key="viaf_107495244" role="ant">Shams al-Dīn Samarqandī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was completed in 1111/1699-1700 with the intention of being presented as a gift in the majlis or gathering of the noble, 
                <persName key="person_f8106" role="dte">Muḥammad Yār Khān</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work comprises a muqaddimah and thirty-five diagrams.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 14r): completed 28 Ramaz̤ān RY 13 of Emperor Muḥammad Shāh, 1143/6 April 1731.</p>
                        <p>Multiple diagrams accommodated within the main text, only the more complicated figures are placed in margins.</p>
                        <p>Nastaʿlīq tending to shikastah āmīz.</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins.</p>
                        <p>Lacuna intervenes in the space between this and the next work.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_51546611">Imām al-Dīn ibn Luṭf Allāh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_51546611">امام الدّين ابن لطف الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23021">Kitāb-i handasah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23021">كتاب هندسه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item2">
                     <locus from="15r" to="16r">ff. 15r-16r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(b), ff. 15r-16r.</p>
                        <p>Excerpt from a work describing Plato’s comments on geometry attributed at the beginning of the passage to 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_19535198" role="aut">“Qāz̤ī Mīr” Ḥusayn ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Maybudī</persName>(911/1504).
                        </p>
                        <p>Dense Arabic annotations in margins.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_19535198">“Qāz̤ī Mīr” Ḥusayn ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Maybudī</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item3">
                     <locus from="17v" to="17v">f. 17v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(c), f. 17v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled diagram showing compound square and rectangular figures linked by intersecting diagonal lines.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item4">
                     <locus from="19r" to="22v">ff. 19r-22v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(d), ff. 19r-22v.</p>
                        <p>Excerpt from an untitled treatise on the geometry of the rectangle attributed to the ‘late’ Mīrzā Khayr Allāh, that is, 
                <persName key="person_f8107" role="aut">Abū al-Khayr Khayr Allāh ibn Luṭf Allāh ibn Aḥmad Lāhawrī the Nādir al-ʿAṣr</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Dense annotations in margins and interlinear spaces.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8107">Abū al-Khayr Khayr Allāh ibn Luṭf Allāh ibn Aḥmad Lāhawrī the Nādir al-ʿAṣr</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item5">
                     <locus from="23r" to="23r">f. 23r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(e), f. 23r.</p>
                        <p>Untitled Arabic note on the geometry of compound squares by an unnamed writer.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Diagram.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item6">
                     <locus from="24r" to="25r">ff. 24r-25r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(f.), ff. 24r-25r.</p>
                        <p>Untitled Arabic treatise on the method for calculating distances between Indian cities and other international sites, by an unnamed author, identified as 
                <persName key="person_f8108" role="aut">al-Ustāz̲ al-mukarram al-mumajjid</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Interlinear annotations.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8108">al-Ustāz̲ al-mukarram al-mumajjid</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item7">
                     <locus from="26r" to="26r">f. 26r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(g), f. 26r.</p>
                        <p>Untitled diagram showing the division of the sphere relative to the locations of 
                <placeName>Dihlī</placeName>and 
                <placeName>Makkah</placeName>, with calculations in margins for relative distances, and additional annotations in Persian describing the figures.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1441B-item8">
                     <locus from="27r" to="27r">f. 27r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1441B(h), f. 27r.</p>
                        <p>Untitled tabular calculations (alphanumerical) of longitude and latitude for the cities and provinces of 
                <placeName>Balkh</placeName>, 
                <placeName>Bukhara</placeName>, 
                <placeName>Tibet</placeName>, 
                <placeName>Kashmir</placeName>, 
                <placeName>Lahore</placeName>, 
                <placeName>Peshawar</placeName>, and 
                <placeName>Multan</placeName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
